Description: Neck and shoulder sherd of Aeolian Black Polychrome pottery oinochoe; fine clay without mica; exterior: from top, below junction of neck and shoulder, frieze of incised tongues alternately added white, black and added red; below,white-red-white-red-white band.
Curator's comments: Fabric from this sherd is almost identical to other Aeolian vessels, in particular, see 1924,1201.11.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.256, no.3)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.56)
